## Files Modified / Created

### Modified

1. `promptnotes/src/lib/domain/capture-auto-save/parse-markdown-to-blocks.ts`
   - Removed module-level `_blockCounter` and global `freshBlockId()` function
   - Added per-call `blockIndex` local counter inside `parseMarkdownToBlocks`
   - Added `nextBlock` closure that increments local counter
   - `makeBlock()` now takes `index: number` parameter instead of calling `freshBlockId()`
   - BlockIds now positional: `block-0`, `block-1`, ... (zero-indexed, reset per call)
   - PROP-025: same input always produces identical Result including BlockId values

2. `promptnotes/src/lib/domain/app-startup/stages.ts`
   - Added imports: `Block` from note types, `BlockParseError` from parse-markdown-to-blocks, `Result` from util
   - Added optional `parseMarkdownToBlocks` field to `ScannedVault` type
   - Field carries the injected block parser from Step 2 for PROP-030 call-budget counting in Step 3

3. `promptnotes/src/lib/domain/app-startup/scan-vault.ts`
   - Added `Block` type import
   - Added `BlockParseError` import from capture-auto-save
   - Added `KNOWN_HYDRATION_REASONS` Set for runtime variant guard
   - Added optional `parseMarkdownToBlocks` port to `ScanVaultPorts`
   - Per-file loop: wrapped `parseNote` call in try/catch (REQ-018 / PROP-028)
   - Added unrecognised-Err-variant folding to `reason:'unknown'` (PROP-028)
   - Added block-parse validation step after `parseNote` succeeds (REQ-017 / PROP-026/PROP-029)
   - Both `Err(BlockParseError)` and `Ok([])` fold to `reason:'block-parse'`
   - `makeUnknownFailure` helper: builds `CorruptedFile` with `reason:'unknown'` from caught exception
   - `blockResultDetail` helper: human-readable BlockParseError description for `detail` field
   - `isKnownHydrationReason` helper: runtime guard for known `HydrationFailureReason` variants
   - Returns `ScannedVault` with `parseMarkdownToBlocks: ports.parseMarkdownToBlocks` (PROP-030)

4. `promptnotes/src/lib/domain/app-startup/hydrate-feed.ts`
   - Added `CorruptedFile` import
   - Added `hydrateNote` import from new `hydrate-note.ts`
   - Per-snapshot loop: calls `hydrateNote(snapshot, blockParser)` or `hydrateNote(snapshot)`
   - Snapshots where `hydrateNote` fails go to `step3CorruptedFiles` with `reason: noteResult.error`
   - Successfully hydrated snapshots build `noteRefs` and `tagInventory`
   - Merges `step2CorruptedFiles` and `step3CorruptedFiles` in the return value
   - PROP-030: uses `scannedVault.parseMarkdownToBlocks` as the block parser for `hydrateNote`

### Created

5. `promptnotes/src/lib/domain/app-startup/hydrate-note.ts` (new file)
   - Pure ACL function: `hydrateNote(snapshot, blockParser?) → Result<Note, HydrationFailureReason>`
   - Default `blockParser` = module-level `parseMarkdownToBlocks` (arity 1, `fn.length === 1`)
   - Calls `blockParser(snapshot.body)` — does NOT call `FrontmatterParser.parse`
   - `Err(BlockParseError)` → `Err('block-parse')`
   - `Ok([])` → `Err('block-parse')` (aggregates.md §1.5 invariant 6)
   - Filters empty paragraph blocks (`paragraph("")`) from parsed results
     (blank-line artifacts from real Markdown files using `\n\n` as separator)
   - Reassigns positional BlockIds (`block-0`, `block-1`, ...) after filtering
   - Remaining blocks built into `Note { id: snapshot.noteId, blocks, frontmatter }`

